Given a maximum of 100 digit numbers as input, find the difference between the sum of odd and even position digits
Test Cases
Case 1
•	Input: 4567
•	Expected Output: 2
Explanation : Odd positions are 4 and 6 as they are pos: 1 and pos: 3, both have sum 10. Similarly, 5 and 7 are at even positions pos: 2 and pos: 4 with sum 12. Thus, difference is 12 – 10 = 2


#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

int main() {

    char num[100];
    int odd_sum = 0;
    int even_sum = 0;

    scanf("%s", num) ; 

    for (int i = 0; num[i] != '\0'; i++) {
    
        int digit = num[i] - '0';

        if (i % 2 == 0) {
            odd_sum += digit;
        } else {
            even_sum += digit;
        }
    }

    int difference = abs(even_sum - odd_sum);

    printf("%d\n", difference);

    return 0;
}
